column5: Heading up to muskoka tomorrow and just wondering if anyone has the goods on lake Rosseau (i know go up and find out for myself ... and I will but I thought I'd ask so I come properly prepared)
I'd cover both,I'm sure the auger would fit in the canoe.

Some guys are planning on putting their huts out on Rosseau this Saturday and with the weekend looking colder than it has been this week, I would bring the auger and some water proof boots to deal with the slush. I called some bait shop up there today and asked about certain lakes, and they all said it just might be good come Saturday, slush should be freezing by then.

There are some fishable spots on Rosseau, John....the spots you usually stop at are okay from what I'm hearing.  Worst case, slide across to the other side, there's a few bays that are solid there    Good luck!
